 Custom KeyStore Type - Optional\: Specifies the type of the Identity keystore. Default value is JKS.
 Custom PrivateKey PassPhrase - Optional\: Specifies the password used to retrieve the private key for WebLogic Server from the Identity keystore.
 Custom TrustStore Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the custom trust store file.

Checks for the existence of a file on the target machine before downloading that file from the Database and Middleware Automation server. For each file in the list\:

(1) Determines whether the file is in the expected location on the target

(2) If the file is not in the expected location, adds that file to a list of files 
 that need to be downloaded.

 Default for UNIX targets is\: sudo su - root /opt/hp/dma/client/bin/jython.sh

 on what the end user wants to do to be hidden or exposed.

 b0559441-92b9-439a-9e28-a57c6a3bfed5.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow installs a new instance of Oracle WebLogic Server using silent mode and a response file. Current supported versions of WebLogic using this workflow are 11g and 12c with either the native installer or the generic installer. If the generic installer is used a JDK supported by the version of WebLogic you are installing must already be installed on the target machine. This workflow will also allow an end user to start or not start the node manager and modifies the node managers property file to enable and configure custom SSL connectivity.


 Results verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the installation was successful. Be sure to also perform the following steps\:

 1. View the {BEAHOME}/logs/log.txt file. This file is created after the installation and contains specific information about what was installed.

 Notification plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails.
 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/weblogic
 Binary Archive - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Weblogic Package Installer. Not required if Java Binary Archived is provided.
 Component Paths - Required\: Specify the components and/or subcomponents you want to install on your system. To install multiple components, separate the components with a bar (|).
 Hostname - Required\: Hostname used to check if node manager is running.
 Log File - Required\: Fully qualified path to a file where the install log will be written.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Setup Custom SSL Stores - Required\: This parameter will set whether you want to run ssl with the demo ssl certificates or with your own custom keystore and truststore. Options are true or false. If true then the hidden parameters Custom KeyStore Path, Custom KeyStore PassPhrase, Custom Truststore Path, Custom TrustStore PassPhrase and Private Key Alias have to be set.
 Staging Directory - Required\: Fully qualified path to a temporary directory that the installer will use to uncompress the binary into.
 Start Node Manager - Required\: This parameter will set whether you want to start the WebLogic Node Manager or not. Options are true or false.
 WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/oracle/weblogic/wlserver12.1

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Weblogic User - *Optional\: User id to install Weblogic software. If not specified 'root' will be used.
 Weblogic Group - *Optional\: Group id to install Weblogic software. If not specified root's group id will be used.
 Java Home - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the JAVA_HOME that will be used for the generic install. Required if generic installer is used. For instance /opt/oracle/jdk1.6.0_35.
